=Being a dung beetle is no easy task. Here kids are enjoying the holiday programme at Addo Elephant National Park, trying to do as dung beetles do. Photo: SUPPLIED Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories What better way to kick off the December school holidays than with a fun-filled, jam-packed, eight day holiday programme at Addo Elephant National Park (AENP)? Well, that s exactly what s in store for not only overnight guests, but day visitors too, during this week until next Wednesday, 14 December.The park s people and conservation staff members have prepared 8 days of excitement to keep youngsters between the ages of 7 and 18 entertained daily between 10:00 and 15:00. They ll be having so much fun that they won t even realise they re learning about nature at the same time!Activities include scavenger hunts, arts and crafts sessions, getting to know the Park, movies, storytelling and a whole lot more! Most of the activities are free of charge, with the only fees payable for day visitors being the conservation fees at the gate. Game drives, which are also on the programme on certain days, are offered at a reduced rate, at only R60 per child (only for the children). The final day s programme will take the form of a Kiddies Christmas Party where parents are requested to bring along a small gift for their child. Please note that some of the activities on the programme may be cancelled owing to inclement weather conditions. No children under the age of 7 years will be allowed to participate without an adult present. Parents should ensure that their children bring lunch packs and bottled water, a hat and comfortable walking shoes.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.